          <div class="blog" id="outer_block_39">
            <h2>Another Experiment in Social Media for Social Good Gets Started</h2>
            <a href="http://social.theciviccommons.com/user/11">
              <img src="http://s3.amazonaws.com/com.theciviccommons.production/avatars/11/large/Photo 96.jpg" class="blog-pic" alt="Noelle Celeeste"/>
            </a>
            <div class='blog_inner'>
              <p>
              Yesterday Jumo launched its <a href="http://www.jumo.com/">beta site</a>.
              </p>
              <p>
              A project sprearheaded by Chris Hughes, co-founder of Facebook and chief digital organizer for Barack Obama, Jumo is
              designed to see if social media can be used to drive volunteerism and donations to causes worldwide.
              </p>
              <p>
              Like Civic Commons is exploring how technology can help build civic engagement by removing barriers and connecting 
              citizens to information and each other, Jumo is testing if creating a place where individuals can connect to non-profits
              and get involved in their work will generate engagement.
              </p>
              <p>
              It's happening all over the country--innovative teams are heading into uncharted territory to find out how by working
              together we can use these powerful tools to connect people to more than entertainment, and in the process strengthen
              our communities.
              </p>
              <p>
              <a href="http://www.nytimes.com/2010/11/30/technology/30jumo.html">
                “The more connected that individual is to an issue they care about, the higher probability there is they will stay involved over a longer period of time,” 
              </a>Mr. Hughes said.
              </p>
              <p>
              Sound familiar?
              </p>
              <p>
              We hope you'll continue to help us test and build Civic Commons so that we can give civic engagement a persistent
              presence in our community.
              </p>
            </div>

            <div class="post_info">
